{
  "stem": "12255.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Isaac Richards.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My birth date is the 23rd of September, 1913, and I was born in Liverpool.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "May I just correct one thing?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not actually a survivor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was not in any of the concentration camps, except in the capacity of a chaplain to the British forces.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Liverpool is a very large city, a port.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the time, it was one of the major ports of England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Jewishly, there were some 7,000 Jewish people who lived in Liverpool.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There must have been quite a lot of synagogue goers, because there were at least five big synagogues, apart from half a dozen smaller what we call [HEBREW], so that people were very well catered for, religiously.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was, of course, a-- a Jewish education, which was usually after school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were no Jewish day schools.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Jewish education was given after the ordinary day school, and attended what was called a cheder.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the normal organizations operated, from the [HEBREW], the [HEBREW], to the helping a poor bride and caring for the poor and the sick, and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the usual institutions of a Jewish community were there in full sway.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We came from what would be called, by modern standards, a pretty orthodox, and certainly observant.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] and such like things were strictly observed in our home, and I think a great majority of the people at that time were-- the older people, certainly, followed that path of life.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, a very large family, by today's standards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I am the seventh child out of eight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At all times, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We indeed, did experience rather rough types of anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
